headline: A Look at Phillips 66’s Valuation Following Strong Third-Quarter Results and Refining Profit Turnaround
summary: Phillips 66 reported impressive third-quarter results that topped revenue and earnings forecasts, leading to a 3% jump in its stock. The company’s refining division returned to profit, supported by stronger market crack spreads. See our latest analysis for Phillips 66. This latest jump extends a strong run for Phillips 66, which has notched a 19.7% share price return so far this year on the back of operational milestones and a brighter business outlook. headline: Brew Oil acquires 14 sites in Iowa
summary: The Midwest retailer purchased 13 c-stores and one smoke shop from local entity Danlee Corp., bringing its footprint to nearly 50 sites across the Hawkeye State.

headline: Phillips 66 completes sale of majority interest in Germany and Austria retail marketing business
summary: HOUSTON, December 01, 2025--Phillips 66 today announced it has closed the sale of a 65 percent interest in its Germany and Austria retail marketing business.
